2ï¸âƒ£ Workspace Settings â€“ What You Can Configure

Core Workspace Settings

Enable/disable:
- Lakehouses
- Notebooks
- Data Pipelines
- Dataflows Gen2

- Git integration
- Deployment pipelines
- Capacity assignment
- Workspace roles (Admin, Member, Contributor, Viewer)

Capacity Settings (Performance)

- Assign Fabric capacity (F2, F4, F8, â€¦)
- Affects:
  - Notebook execution
  - Pipeline scheduling
  - Concurrency
  - Pausing behavior

Performance tuning = capacity size + concurrency control

Security & Governance

- Private endpoints (network security)
- Managed identities (item-level)
- Role-based access control (RBAC)

